cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper discusses the use of pre-trained language models for natural language processing tasks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also focuses on improving the performance of multilingual models, which could be considered a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The tasks evaluated in the paper, such as named entity recognition and machine reading comprehension, also have relevance to natural language processing and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions machine translation quality estimation, which could be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves analyzing and generating images of text.
